The small train dataset has 6 times as many rows as the full dataset. Based on the tidy-tuesday README this seems to be because delay causes are gathered for the small trains data. Can we prove this by picking a particular route, e.g.Paris Est to Metz in a particular month

Which routes have the longest journeys?

route_journey_times <- full_trains %>% 
  group_by(departure_station, arrival_station) %>% 
  summarise(
    # journey_time_q1 = quantile(journey_time_avg, 0.25, na.rm = TRUE),
    # journey_time_q3 = quantile(journey_time_avg, 0.75, na.rm = TRUE),
    # journey_time_median = median(journey_time_avg, na.rm = TRUE),
    # journey_time_sd = sd(journey_time_avg, na.rm = TRUE),
    journey_time_avg = mean(journey_time_avg, na.rm = TRUE)
  ) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(
    journey_time_avg_overall = mean(journey_time_avg),
    journey_time_diff = journey_time_avg - journey_time_avg_overall,
    route = paste(departure_station, arrival_station, sep = " to "),
    international = factor(
      case_when(
        str_detect(route, "Madrid") ~ 1,
        str_detect(route, "Barcelona") ~ 1,
        str_detect(route, "Italie") ~ 1,
        TRUE ~ 0
      )
    )
  ) %>% 
  select(route, international, journey_time_avg, journey_time_diff)

longest_routes <- route_journey_times %>% 
  top_n(5, wt = journey_time_avg)
  
shortest_routes <- route_journey_times %>%
  top_n(-5, wt = journey_time_avg)

top_bottom <- bind_rows(longest_routes, shortest_routes)

top_bottom %>% 
  mutate(route = fct_reorder(route, journey_time_diff)) %>% 
  arrange(journey_time_diff) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(route, journey_time_diff, fill = journey_time_diff > 0)) +
  geom_col() +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    legend.position = "none",
    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10),
    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10),
    plot.title = element_text(size = 16, face = "bold"),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(size = 11),
    panel.grid.major.y = element_blank()
  ) +
  labs(
    title = "Longest and shortest train journeys",
    subtitle = "Compared to average journey time",
    x = "",
    y = "Difference from average (minutes)"
  )

Which route station has the worst punctuality?

full_trains %>% 
  group_by(departure_station) %>% 
  summarise(
    total_num_trips = sum(total_num_trips, na.rm = TRUE),
    num_late_at_departure = sum(num_late_at_departure),
    percent_late = num_late_at_departure / total_num_trips
  ) %>% 
  mutate(departure_station = fct_reorder(departure_station, percent_late)) %>% 
  top_n(10, wt = percent_late) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(departure_station, percent_late)) +
  geom_col(fill = "deepskyblue2") +
  geom_text(aes(label = paste0(round(percent_late * 100, 1),"%")), fontface = "bold", colour = "white", hjust=1.2) +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = percent_format()) + 
  theme(
    legend.position = "none",
    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10),
    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10),
    plot.title = element_text(size = 16, face = "bold"),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(size = 11),
    panel.grid.major.y = element_blank()
  ) +
  labs(
    title = "What's the hold up?",
    subtitle = "Which station are you most likely to be delayed from",
    x = "",
    y = "Departed late (%)"
  )

full_trains %>% 
  group_by(departure_station) %>% 
  summarise(
    total_num_trips = sum(total_num_trips, na.rm = TRUE),
    num_late_at_departure = sum(num_late_at_departure),
    percent_late = num_late_at_departure / total_num_trips
  ) %>% 
  mutate(departure_station = fct_reorder(departure_station, percent_late)) %>% 
  top_n(10, wt = total_num_trips)

full_trains %>% 
  group_by(departure_station) %>% 
  summarise(
    total_num_trips = sum(total_num_trips, na.rm = TRUE),
    num_late_at_departure = sum(num_late_at_departure)
  ) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(
    percent_late = num_late_at_departure / total_num_trips,
    departure_station = fct_reorder(departure_station, percent_late)
  ) %>% 
  filter(total_num_trips > 25000) %>% 
  top_n(10, wt = percent_late) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(departure_station, percent_late)) +
  geom_col(fill = "deepskyblue2") +
  geom_text(aes(label = paste0(round(percent_late * 100, 1),"%")), fontface = "bold", colour = "white", hjust=1.2) +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = percent_format(accuracy = 1)) + 
  theme(
    legend.position = "none",
    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10),
    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10),
    plot.title = element_text(size = 16, face = "bold"),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(size = 11),
    panel.grid.major.y = element_blank()
  ) +
  labs(
    title = "What's the hold up?",
    subtitle = "Which station are you most likely to be delayed from (at least 25,000 journeys)",
    x = "",
    y = "Departed late (%)"
  )

## Which of Lyon Part Dieu routes proved the worst for delays?

## Lyon Part Dieu delays by year

full_trains %>% 
  group_by(date) %>% 
  mutate(
    overall_percent_late = sum(num_late_at_departure) / sum(total_num_trips, na.rm = TRUE)
  ) %>% 
  filter(departure_station == "Lyon Part Dieu") %>% 
  summarise(
    total_num_trips = sum(total_num_trips, na.rm = TRUE),
    num_late_at_departure = sum(num_late_at_departure),
    percent_late = num_late_at_departure / total_num_trips,
    overall_percent_late = mean(overall_percent_late)
  ) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  select(date, "Lyon Part Dieu" = percent_late, "Overall" = overall_percent_late) %>% 
  gather(key = "station", value = "percent_late", -date) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(date, percent_late, colour = station)) +
  geom_line() +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = percent_format(accuracy = 1)) +
  theme_minimal()

full_trains %>% 
  group_by(departure_station, arrival_station) %>% 
  summarise(
    total_num_trips = sum(total_num_trips, na.rm = TRUE),
    num_late_at_departure = sum(num_late_at_departure),
    num_of_canceled_trains = sum(num_of_canceled_trains)
  ) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(
    percent_late = num_late_at_departure / total_num_trips,
    percent_cancelled = num_of_canceled_trains / total_num_trips,
    route = paste(departure_station, arrival_station, sep = " to "),
    route = fct_reorder(route, percent_cancelled)
  ) %>% 
  # filter(total_num_trips > 25000) %>% 
  top_n(10, wt = percent_cancelled) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(route, percent_cancelled, fill = str_detect(route, "Marseille"))) +
  geom_col() +
  geom_text(aes(label = paste0(round(percent_cancelled * 100, 1),"%")), fontface = "bold", colour = "white", hjust=1.2) +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = percent_format()) + 
  theme(
    legend.position = "none",
    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10),
    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10),
    plot.title = element_text(size = 16, face = "bold"),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(size = 11),
    panel.grid.major.y = element_blank()
  ) +
  labs(
    title = "Highest cancellation percentage",
    subtitle = "At least 25,000 journeys",
    x = "",
    y = "Cancelled (%)"
  )

fill_colours_manual = c("azure3", "deepskyblue4")
theme_set(theme_minimal())

top_delay_stations <- full_trains %>%
  group_by(departure_station) %>% 
  summarize(
    total_trips = sum(total_num_trips),
    delays = sum(num_late_at_departure)
  ) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(
    overall_num_delays = sum(delays),
    percent_all_delays = delays / overall_num_delays,
    lyon = ifelse(departure_station == "Lyon Part Dieu", T, F)
  ) %>% 
  mutate(
    departure_station = fct_reorder(departure_station, percent_all_delays)
  ) %>% 
  top_n(10, percent_all_delays)

top_delay_stations %>% 
  mutate(departure_station = fct_reorder(departure_station, total_trips)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(departure_station, total_trips, fill = lyon)) +
  geom_col() +
  geom_text(aes(label = paste(round(total_trips / 1000, 1), "k")), fontface = "bold", colour = "white", hjust=1.2) +
  coord_flip() +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = comma_format()) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = fill_colours_manual) +
  theme(
    legend.position = "none",
    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10),
    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10),
    plot.title = element_text(size = 16),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(size = 11, face = "bold"),
    panel.grid.major.y = element_blank()
  ) +
  labs(
    title = "Total number of trips",
    subtitle = "Lyon Part Dieu is the 3rd busiest station",
    x = "",
    y = "Total trips"
  )

top_delay_stations %>%
